The Perceptron
[ 154 ]
Our goal is to train a perceptron that can classify animals using the two real-valued
features. We will represent kittens with the positive class and adult cats with the negative
class. Our perceptron has three input units. x_1 is the input unit for the bias term. x_2 and
x_3 are input units for the two features. Our perceptron's computational unit uses the unit
step activation function. In this example, we will set the maximum number of training
epochs to ten; if the algorithm does not converge within ten epochs, it will stop and return
the current values of the weights. For simplicity, we will set the learning rate to 1. Initially,
we will set all of the weights to 0. Let's examine the first training epoch, which is shown in
the following table:
